At 12:09 AM 4/16/2003 -0400, you wrote:
>Well, as expected (same on my other engine) all pistons pins are somewhat 
>stuck, they turn freely in the piston and in the rod bushing but they 
>won't come out easily pass the C-Ring. The one my my other engine were a 
>pain in the but to remove, i had to bang those one very hard, i don't want 
>to do the same with the one in my working engine.

Bob Hoover has instructions for making a simple wrist pin puller.
I made one for myself, in about a half hour--works great.

http://osf02.ktu.edu.tr/~ulutas/hoover/pistonpins.html

